title: Technical Sergeant
description: Provide augmentation support to USSOCOM supporting OEF/OIF/OCO via monitoring of telecommunications to include telephone, e-mail, and pagers. Supervised 15 person team and conducted Communications Security (COMSEC) and intelligence gathering efforts supporting JSOTFs in the Middle East and Africa. Delivered Operations Security (OPSEC) training to members of the military and intelligence communities. Monitored and reviewed raw (voice) and digital communications; filed and authored daily reports. Provide Signal Security (SIGSEC) assessments during USSOCOM execution of sensitive Secretary of Defense (SECDEF) and Joint Chiefs of Staff (JCS) directed exercises. Duties and Tasks Used NSA software & databases, including ONEROOF UIS, for interpreting and reviewing Kleighlight (KL) and GistQueue (GQ) products. Produced daily tactical intelligence reports highlighting vulnerabilities meeting commanders’ priority intelligence requirements (PIR). Used signals intelligence (SIGINT) tools and databases to develop pattern of life (POL) analysis, such as IC Reach, FIRETRUCK, Cultweave, SKOPE Tools, Association, and cellular exploitation (CELLEX) techniques; constructed call-chain diagrams in Analyst’s Notebook for social networking analysis (SNA). Used various communications networks and programs, such as NSA Net, JWICS, SIPRnet, the JSOC Information Automated Network (JIANT), the Special Operations Intelligence System (SOIS), and military internet relay char (mIRC), for information sharing and coordination.
name: Nicole Johnson
